### 16.3.2 Writing System Properties

To modify the existing set of system properties, use\xA0System.setProperties. This method takes a\xA0Properties\xA0object that has been initialized to contain the properties to be set. This method replaces the entire set of system properties with the new set represented by the\xA0Properties\xA0object.

**Warning:**\xA0Changing system properties is potentially dangerous and should be done with discretion. Many system properties are not reread after start-up and are there for informational purposes. Changing some properties may have unexpected side-effects.

